  "prompt": "Why do clicks from Quora come up as direct traffic in my Google Analytics reports?",
  "response": "Clicks from Quora often appear as direct traffic in Google Analytics due to several reasons:\n\n1. Referral Tracking Limitations\n- Quora may not pass referral information consistently\n- The platform may strip out referral source tracking parameters\n\n2. Technical Routing\n- Quora might route links through an intermediate page or redirect\n- This can cause UTM parameters to be lost in the process\n\n3. Link Characteristics\n- Some Quora links might use JavaScript-based redirects\n- These can prevent proper tracking of the original source\n\n4. Analytics Configuration\n- Your Google Analytics tracking might not be configured to capture all referral sources\n- Some tracking settings can inadvertently categorize Quora clicks as direct traffic\n\nTo improve tracking:\n\n- Use UTM parameters when posting Quora links\n- Ensure Google Analytics referral settings are correctly configured\n- Consider using Google's Campaign URL Builder\n- Set up custom tracking in Google Analytics\n- Check your website's tracking implementation\n\nIf you want precise tracking, you might need to manually tag Quora links or use advanced analytics configurations to capture the source accurately.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
